cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper is about improving recommendation performance in recommender systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves a rating transformation model, which is a machine learning technique, and thus falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses user behavior and preferences, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the experiments are conducted on real-world datasets, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
